gmx trjconv -f md.xtc -s md.tpr -o mdcenter.xtc -center -pbc nojump

It manipulates the protein's trajectory across frames, centering it and preventing “jumps” within the simulation “box.”

gmx make_ndx -f protein.gro -o index.ndx

Allows the selection of specific atoms to generate the principal components.

gmx covar -s 6eqeions.gro -f mdcenter.xtc -n index.ndx -o eigenval.xvg -v eigenvec.trr -av averange.pdb

Calculates the covariance matrix.

gmx anaeig -s 6eqeions.gro -f mdcenter.xtc -n index.ndx -v eigenvec.trr -first 1 -last 2 -2d -proj proj.xvg

Projection onto Eigenvectors
Input: mdcenter.xtc (trajectory), eigenvec.trr (eigenvectors)
Output: proj.xvg (projection of the trajectory onto the first PCs)
Options:
-first 1 -last 2: Uses the first 2 eigenvectors (PC1, PC2)
-2d: Generates a 2D projection (PC1 vs. PC2)

xmgrace 2dproj.xvg

Opens the 2dproj.xvg file in Grace (plotting tool)
Displays a 2D plot of the PC1-PC2 points

